		<section>
			<div>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">Jobs in the Food Industry</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					India is a hub for food processing, and there are plenty of food industry jobs available, catering to various skill sets. If you are passionate about ensuring the quality of food and contributing to the food industry's growth, then jobs in the food processing industry may be the perfect fit for you. The food industry is a dynamic and ever-changing field that is constantly on the lookout for fresh talent to innovate and drive its growth. There are plenty of food industry jobs available for experienced as well as freshers. If you are a fresh graduate with a background in food technology, there are plenty of opportunities for you to explore. Whether it be in quality control or product development, the food industry offers an array of exciting career paths. 
				</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					Keeping that in purview, FICSI has developed India's first job portal for Food Processing Industries.
				</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					Those who are interested to look out for jobs in the food processing industry can upload their CV and reach out to potential employers in the food production and food processing industries through a single window portal. The job portal allows you to-
				</p>
				<ol class="list-disc pl-5">
					<li>Search jobs under desired job roles across various sub-sectors</li>
					<li>Regularly update your qualifications after completing a new food safety course</li>
					<li>Get notified about new jobs that match your profile</li>
				</ol>
				<br>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">A Trusted Platform for Quality Jobs in The Food Industry</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					Food Industry Capacity and Skill Initiative (FICSI) is an organization that provides a platform for young professionals to connect with industry leaders and gain specialized training to establish themselves in the sector. Be it jobs for food technology freshers, quality assurance jobs in the food sector, or quality control jobs in the food industry, you will find them all here. So, if you have a passion for food and an eagerness to learn, the food industry is the perfect place for you to start your career journey.
				</p>
				<p>
					Food quality control jobs in the food industry involve inspecting products, ensuring they meet certain standards, and making sure they are safe for consumption. Freshers in this field can also explore careers in product development, food processing, and research and development. Quality assurance jobs in the food industry are also in high demand as companies are always seeking to meet and exceed industry standards. FICSI is a great resource for those looking to build their careers in the food industry. With so many exciting opportunities available, the food industry is definitely a field to consider for freshers looking to make their mark. Joining the FICSI can also provide valuable resources and networking opportunities to help you succeed in your career.
				</p>
				<br>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">Opportunities for Employers</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					FICI has a state-of-the-art job portal for fulfilling the rising demand for skilled manpower in the food production and food processing industries. Employers can benefit from our job portal in the following ways-
				</p>
				<ol class="list-disc pl-5">
					<li>Get access to a pool of skilled manpower</li>
					<li>Hire candidates based on experience, expertise, and specific job roles</li>
					<li>Use the platform for branding</li>
				</ol>
				<br>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">Opportunities for Students/Employees</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					Who are interested to join food processing industry can upload their CV and reach out to potential employers in the food production and food processing industries through a single window portal. The job portal allows you to:
				</p>
				<ol class="list-disc pl-5">
					<li>Search jobs under desired job roles across various sub-sectors</li>
					<li>Regularly update your qualifications after completing a new food safety course</li>
					<li>Get notified about new jobs that match your profile</li>
				</ol>
				<br>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">National Food Processing Aptitude Test</p>
				<p>
					In order to identify the best minds to work in the industry FICSI conducts, at least twice a year, a National Food Processing Aptitude Test for Food Tech graduates in their final semesters. The test is online, scientifically designed, and is conducted on a modern AI-enabled assessment portal. The test includes food processing fundamentals, food safety and hygiene, logical reasoning, and IT basics.
				</p>
				<br>
				<p class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl mb-3">Career Fair</p>
				<p class="mb-3">
					FICSI conducts a Career Fair at least twice a year providing the industry a platform for recruitment. Food tech graduates having 0-2 years of experience are generally eligible. This initiative is fast becoming a one-stop recruitment solution for the industry. The fair is mounted on a versatile online platform that gives HR managers space to interact in privacy with prospective employees.
				</p>
				<p>
					FICSI facilitates Pradhan Mantri National Apprenticeship Mela(PMNAM) and Rozgar Mela organized by NSDC.
				</p>
